Detection Logic

Detect a successful login following multiple failed attempts.

Splunk Query
index=linux sourcetype=secure
("Failed password" OR "Accepted password")
| rex "from (?<src_ip>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+)"
| transaction src_ip maxspan=5m
| search "Accepted password"
Why This Matters

Attackers often succeed after brute forcing credentials.

SOC analysts always ask:

Did a success follow the failures?
